    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-01-14T15:55:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-14T15:55:00-05:00" n="382"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d382">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">683.84A/12–2751: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 382<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Israel</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d382fn1">Repeated to Damascus, Amman, Jerusalem, Paris, and
                        Beirut.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-01-14T15:55:00-05:00"
                            >January 14, 1952—3:55 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>490. Dept appreciates helpful comments contained Tel Aviv <gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 627 Dec 27<note n="2" xml:id="d382fn2"
                        >See <ref target="#d381fn3">footnote 3, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> and Damascus <gloss target="#t_Legtel1">Legtel</gloss> 408
                    Jan 9. Dept sincerely hopes change in Israel attitude will follow as result
                        <persName corresp="#p_EAS1">Eban</persName>’s visit and Emb representations.
                    Dept considers paramount importance Syrian-Israel <gloss target="#t_MAC1"
                        >MAC</gloss> resume mtgs. Chairman <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss> has
                    sufficient auth deal with questions he considers shld be discussed.</p>
                <p>Dept concurs fully Emb and Leg views that intervention with Syrian Govt effect
                    release Israel prisoners undesirable and inappropriate <pb facs="0917" n="877"
                        xml:id="pg_877"/> at this time, particularly since this precisely type
                    problem <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss> estab to consider. Suggest Emb reply
                    to <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> contained Emb <gloss target="#t_desp1"
                        >desp</gloss> [<hi rend="italic">telegram</hi>] 578 Dec 13<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d382fn3">See <ref target="#d381fn6">footnote 6, <hi rend="italic"
                                >supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> to effect that this question shld be considered in <gloss
                        target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss>. While Dept unwilling intervene directly with
                    Syrian Govt effect release these Israelis, since problem matter for <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> machinery, it will recommend Leg Damascus urge
                    Syrian Govt resume <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss> mtgs soonest. Dept
                    considers it may be desirable that on <persName corresp="#p_RLG1"
                        >Riley</persName>’s return <gloss target="#t_NE1">NE</gloss> he personally
                    take charge <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss> mtgs discuss this question in
                    order effect release Israelis in Syria.</p>
                <p>Leg Damascus its discretion might inform Syrian Govt US gratified at dispatch and
                    relative amity with which Syrian-Israel <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss>
                    dealt with shooting two Israelis Lake Tiberias and hopes other matters
                    outstanding can be discussed soonest in <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss>; wld
                    urge Syrians to cooperate with <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> in holding
                        <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss> mtgs on regular basis and US likewise
                    urging Israelis to do same.</p>
                <p>Dept hopes <persName corresp="#p_RLG1">Riley</persName> can return <gloss
                        target="#t_NE1">NE</gloss> soonest.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
